Even as it reiterated its intention to purchase Enron Corp., Dynegy Inc. is =
coming under increasing pressure to renegotiate or walk away from the multib=
illion-dollar deal.=20
The pressure is stemming from the continuing slide in the price of Enron sha=
res and the mounting financial problems at the Houston energy-trading compan=
y, the nation's biggest marketer of electricity and natural gas. During the =
past month, Enron has taken a $1 billion write-off of assets, revised downwa=
rd the earnings of the past several years and taken a $1.2 billion reduction=
 in shareholder equity.
The problems have been due largely to dealings Enron had with private partne=
rships, run by some of its own executives, under investigation by the Securi=
ties and Exchange Commission. In an SEC filing Monday, Enron disclosed hundr=
eds of millions of potential additional write-offs as well as the possibilit=
y that its weakening financial condition could force it to repay more than $=
2 billion in loans by the end of the year.=20
