hares fell $1.98, or 28%, to $5.01 each after having dropped 23% Tuesday. In=
 excess of 115 million shares traded Wednesday, more than four times the vol=
ume of any other Big Board stock. Enron's bonds also again traded sharply lo=
wer, market observers said.=20
