Enron Corp., the embattled Houston energy and trading company, has been sued=
 by members of its employee-retirement plan, which has suffered losses becau=
se of Enron's plummeting stock price.=20
Two separate lawsuits, filed in federal court in Houston, allege Enron misle=
d participants in its 401(k) retirement plan about the risks of investing in=
 the company's shares and note that the company forced the employees to rema=
in invested in its stock even as the shares fell. Amid growing disclosures o=
f financial problems in recent weeks, the company "locked down" the retireme=
nt plan from Oct. 17 to Nov. 19 to make administrative changes, which preven=
ted employees from selling Enron shares as the share price collapsed.
